YouTube creators have noticed their Shorts look different on the platform compared to Instagram, sparking accusations of secret AI upscaling. YouTube later admitted to running a test using “traditional machine learning” to sharpen and denoise videos, but many creators argue it makes content look overprocessed and raises questions about creator control. Linus and Luke discuss what this means for creators and whether YouTube has crossed the line.
